CSC 315 Polygon Tesselation Project

The goal of this project was to implement the ear-clipping algorithm of tesselation to a polygon that the user drew.

To compile: make project
To run: project

Left-click to end polygon
Right-click to add point to polygon
Hit f or F to fill the polygon with no tesselation after it has been built
Hit l or L to return to the original outline of the polygon after it has been built
Hit p or P to fill the polygon after the polygon has been built and tesselated
Hit t or T to run to tesselate the polygon, giving you the triangles on the screen, the triangle points, and the trianlg area
Hit q or Q to quit the program